{
  "description": "A vibrant image captures a hummingbird delicately feeding from the vibrant red and green blossoms of a flax plant. The bird is positioned mid-flight, its wings blurred, as it extends its beak into one of the tubular flowers. The flax plant's flower spike is a rich, reddish-brown hue, with numerous buds and open blossoms clustered around a dark central stem. The background is a soft, blurred green, suggesting foliage and natural sunlight filtering through trees, creating bokeh effects. The scene is a display of natural beauty and the symbiotic relationship between the bird and the plant.",
